HEADWORD: Church-ale
<hw>Church"-ale`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A church or
parish festival (as in commemoration of the dedication of a church), at
which much ale was used.</def> <rj><au>Wright. Nares.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

